Senior Petroleum Engineer
Job Seekers
|
|
what:
where:
Abu Dhabi
My client is a major oil operator based in Abu Dhabi. They are currently seeking a Senior Petroleum Engineer to join them on a staff basis. The client are rapidly expanding all of their departments and need this person to provide specialist advice and unique expertise in Petroleum Engineering activities.
To be successful for this role, you must be very knowledgeable in the following areas: Reviewing detailed proposals for activities and studies for all Asset Teams and recommending available alternatives. Reviewing relevant reports and documents prior to submission to shareholders. Reviewing application of new technology, including directing and participating in feasibility studies to recommend adoption of new techniques and equipment. Recommending and planning for special tests or test runs prior to recommending field wide implementation Reviews methods currently in use and if needed initiates the development of standard methods to enhance work processes in expertise area Knowing the company's health, safety and environmental policy, procedures, regulations and objectives. Knowledge of well completion and design, stimulation, well and system performance, artificial lift, rig less operations and coiled tubing applications, corrosion, scale and metering is necessary for this role.
The ideal candidate for the Senior Petroleum Engineer role will currently hold a minimum of BSc degree in Petroleum Engineering or a related area. A total of at least 15 years experience in Petroleum Engineering is required, with a minimum of 8 of these years being hands on and practical. The company are offering a brilliant salary level for this role, and additionally a full, ex-pat package. If this is the kind of role you would be perfect for, please apply today by following the onscreen links! This job was originally posted as
